\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. V. obliqua} Hill, {\i Hort. Kew. }316 (1768) ({\i V. cucullata} Aiton). Glabrous or very sparsely pubescent. Lamina ovate-cordate with an open sinus, acute, crenate, about 1/3 as long as petiole. Peduncles equalling or exceeding leaves. Flowers c. 2 cm, blue-violet, not fragrant. Sepals acute; calycine appendages 2-6 mm. Style capitate. Cleistogamous fruit 1-1·5 cm, ovoid-cylindrical, only slightly exceeding sepals.{\i  Naturalized from gardens in Switzerland and Italy}. [He It.] ({\i North America}.)
