\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. MELANIUM Ging. Herbaceous. Stipules usually large, leaf-like, often divided. Lateral petals directed upwards. Open flowers blue or yellow; cleistogamous flowers not produced. Style geniculate at the base, capitate, with wide stigmatic aperture. Capsule erect at maturity, glabrous.
