\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. V. crassiuscula} Bory, {\i Ann. Gén. Sci. Phys.} ({\i Bruxelles}) {\b 3}: 16 (1820) ({\i V. nevadensis} Boiss.). Caespitose perennial up to 15 cm. Leaves c. 1·5 cm, ovate-orbicular, entire, glabrous or very shortly pubescent; petiole slightly longer than lamina. Stipules entire, like the leaves but smaller. Peduncles 2-4 cm. Flowers 1-1·5 cm, bright violet, pink or whitish, the lower petal golden-yellow at the base. Spur very short, obtuse, only slightly exceeding calycine appendages.{\i  Open habitats above} 2500{\i  m. S. Spain} ({\i Sierra Nevada}). Hs.
