\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. V. diversifolia} (DC.) W. Becker, {\i Bull. Herb. Boiss}. ser. 2,{\b  3}: 892 (1903). Caespitose perennial 3-8(-15) cm, covered with rather short, stiff hairs. Leaves 1-2 cm, forming a rosette, entire; the lower suborbicular or broadly ovate, the upper ovate-oblong. Stipules oblong, with 3 laciniae. Peduncles 2-4 cm. Flowers up to 2 cm, violet, fragrant. Spur c. 5 mm, subulate, curved, greatly exceeding calycine appendages.{\i  Alpine meadows and rocks. • E. and C. Pyrenees.} Ga Hs.
